From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: android-tools-builder <builder@localhost>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] adb: map local sockets to Linux abstract namespace

Rockchip's closed NPU transfer client forwards local:transfer_proxy while
rknn_server listens on the Linux abstract socket @transfer_proxy. Android
adbd maps local: to the reserved /dev/socket namespace, but that convention
does not describe standalone Linux services.

Keep Android and host adb behavior unchanged. Only the standalone Linux adbd
target maps the legacy local: alias to the abstract namespace.
---
 socket_spec.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/socket_spec.cpp b/socket_spec.cpp
index 2f03552..ff93db5 100644
--- a/socket_spec.cpp
+++ b/socket_spec.cpp
@@ -69,5 +69,7 @@ static auto& kLocalSocketTypes = *new std::unordered_map<std::string, LocalSocket
 #if ADB_HOST
     { "local", { ANDROID_SOCKET_NAMESPACE_FILESYSTEM, !ADB_WINDOWS } },
+#elif defined(ADB_STANDALONE_LINUX)
+    { "local", { ANDROID_SOCKET_NAMESPACE_ABSTRACT, ADB_LINUX } },
 #else
     { "local", { ANDROID_SOCKET_NAMESPACE_RESERVED, !ADB_WINDOWS } },
 #endif
